<font size=5 face="arial"><b>Policies</b></font>
<p>
<font face="arial"><b>Book Return Policy</b></font>
<br>
<ul>
<li>Returns must be accompanied by the original receipt or invoice.
<li>Textbook returns will be accepted through the first two weeks of the semester or two weeks from the date of purchase, whichever is longer.  No returns will be accepted after April first and November first of the respective semesters.  During Summer Session school books may only be returned during the first three days of class.
<li>Trade (general) and special order books are non-returnable.
<li>The University of Idaho Bookstore is the sole judge in determining whether books returned are in new or used condition.
<li>Course packs are returnable following the textbook rules unless they are special ordered.  Special ordered course packs are non-returnable.
</ul>

<p>

<font face="arial"><b>Supply Return Policy</b></font>
<br>
Within two weeks (14 days) from the date of purchase the supply department will replace, exchange or refund the purchase price under the following conditions:
<ul>
<li>Sales receipt must be presented.
<li>Items must be new and in salable condition.
<li>The University of Idaho Bookstore will replace any defective calculator within two weeks (14 days) of the date of purchase.  After two weeks defective calculators must be returned to the factory or the nearest service center for repair.  Addresses are located in the instruction booklets.
</ul>
<p>

